{"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"roleHeading":"Instance Property","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}],"title":"overlayBounds","symbolKind":"property","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}],"externalID":"c:objc(pl)MLNOverlay(py)overlayBounds","role":"symbol"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"]]},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"readonly"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@MLNCoordinateBounds","text":"MLNCoordinateBounds","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}],"platforms":["iOS"],"languages":["occ"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This property contains the smallest rectangle that completely encompasses the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"overlay. Implementers of this protocol must set this area when implementing"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"their overlay class, and after setting it, you must not change it."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If this overlay spans the antimeridian, its bounds may extend west of −180 degrees","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"longitude or east of 180 degrees longitude. For example, an overlay covering the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Pacific Ocean from Tokyo to San Francisco might have a bounds extending","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"from (35.68476, −220.24257) to (37.78428, −122.41310).","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"occ","url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds"},"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNCoordinateBounds":{"type":"topic","title":"MLNCoordinateBounds","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlncoordinatebounds","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"A rectangular area as measured on a two-dimensional map projection.","type":"text"}],"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNCoordinateBounds"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNOverlay"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay","role":"symbol","title":"MLNOverlay"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"kind":"symbol","identifier":